# Change records — the durable, discoverable audit trail of every change (#42).
# `.architecture/` (design: TDD, ADRs, work-packages, contracts, probe output),
# `.specifications/` (requirements), and `.changes/` (per-change manifests) ALL
# travel with the change branch, so review, the next session, and the founder
# can read WHY the code is the way it is. These are records of the change, not
# generated noise — they belong in the repo. (Per-worktree scratch — the
# `.wpx-*` / `.executor-*-dev-sha` sidecars — is still ignored by the filename
# patterns further down, even inside `.architecture/`.)
#
# (Previously `.architecture/` + `.specifications/` were ignored except a
# couple of re-included dirs; #42 reverses that — durable by default.)

# Concierge journey state — per-project session state, not a change record.
.concierge/

# Note: `.context/` (the context index) and `.security/` (viability reports)
# are ALSO durable change records (#42) and travel with the change branch —
# they are intentionally NOT ignored.

# Worktrees (defensive — should never be inside the repo)
wp-*-worktree/

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# Python (for marketplace tooling)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Node (for marketplace tooling)
node_modules/

# Executor sidecar files — per-worktree scratch, must never travel onto dev
# (L-07: .wpx-base-sha nearly leaked onto dev via a worktree commit)
.wpx-base-sha
.executor-*-dev-sha
.wpx-*

# Logs / scratch
*.log
.scratch/
